like this to the committee.

11:07.200 --> 11:08.533
We have executive --

11:08.535 --> 11:10.602
If I hear the words
"executive privilege"

11:10.604 --> 11:12.537
Come out of your mouth
one more time...

11:12.539 --> 11:14.472
What? Did someone give you
a list of buzzwords

11:14.474 --> 11:15.607
When you took this job?

11:15.609 --> 11:17.375
Things to say
so that you sound like

11:17.377 --> 11:19.144
You knew how to
help run a country?

11:19.146 --> 11:21.846
Stuff just spitting out randomly
to people?

11:21.848 --> 11:23.648
Do you say these buzzwords
to putin?

11:23.650 --> 11:26.651
Uh, mr. President,
d-do you let this woman

11:26.653 --> 11:28.553
Anywhere near
the prime minister?

11:28.555 --> 11:30.722
Because I know david,
and he would eat her for lunch.

11:30.724 --> 11:32.524
Patricia.

11:32.526 --> 11:35.160
You're testifying, sir.
The president is testifying.

11:35.162 --> 11:36.961
I am not asking.
I am telling.

11:36.963 --> 11:39.030
-End of story.
-Okay.

11:39.032 --> 11:41.132
Sir, I just don't think
we should

11:41.134 --> 11:42.901
Bend over backwards
to cooperate with --

11:42.903 --> 11:46.738
There is cooperating
and then there's cooperating,

11:46.740 --> 11:48.973
Which is why our forefathers
invented discovery documents.

11:48.975 --> 11:51.509
I want to gather
every stupid file

11:51.511 --> 11:54.045
Out of every stupid file room
and send them to the committee.

11:54.047 --> 11:55.413
All files.

11:55.415 --> 11:57.682
I want trucks full of files
pulling out of the gates.

11:57.684 --> 11:59.317
What are you doing?

11:59.319 --> 12:00.985
These are just some menus from
the fourth of july barbecue.

12:00.987 --> 12:02.721
Yes, I know that,
but put them back in there.

12:02.723 --> 12:05.457
Ma'am?
Stop thinking
and keep stuffing.

12:06.159 --> 12:08.226
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

12:08.228 --> 12:10.161
Mellie: Let me guess.
White house document dump.

12:10.163 --> 12:12.897
We asked for digital files,
but instead we got these.

12:12.899 --> 12:14.432
And apparently
there's still more to come.

12:14.434 --> 12:17.368
This is all just a cute attempt
to stall our investigation.

12:17.370 --> 12:20.205
It also makes them look like
they have something to hide.

12:20.207 --> 12:21.439
We should cart these over to
the senate gallery,

12:21.441 --> 12:22.841
Hold a press conference,

12:22.843 --> 12:24.676
And show the american people
how scared and sneaky

12:24.678 --> 12:25.877
This white house
is behaving.

12:25.879 --> 12:28.012
-I'm sorry. "we"?
-Well, not just us.

12:28.014 --> 12:29.547
The whole committee,
of course.

12:29.549 --> 12:31.549
You do realize
you have to recuse yourself

12:31.551 --> 12:32.784
From this investigation?

12:32.786 --> 12:34.552
Recuse myself?

12:34.554 --> 12:36.020
Yeah, and resign
from the committee.

12:36.022 --> 12:37.222
Conflict of interest
is as clear --

12:37.224 --> 12:39.524
This investigation
is far bigger

12:39.526 --> 12:41.359
Than my relationship
with the president.

12:41.361 --> 12:43.094
I represent
the people of virginia.

12:43.096 --> 12:45.029
You can't expect me
to step down from --

12:45.031 --> 12:46.197
Mellie, you're
in the middle

12:46.199 --> 12:47.365
Of divorcing the man
we're investigating.

12:47.367 --> 12:48.867
Your presence on the committee
would be highly --

12:48.869 --> 12:51.069
A distraction,
a sideshow.

12:51.071 --> 12:53.138
It would taint
an already salacious --

12:53.140 --> 12:55.440
I am not some scorned woman
bitching about my ex.

12:55.442 --> 12:58.076
I am a senator and a member
of the judiciary committee.

12:58.078 --> 12:59.644
As far as the american people
are concerned,

12:59.646 --> 13:01.546
You<i> are</i> a scorned woman
bitching about your ex.

13:01.548 --> 13:03.915
End of story.

13:03.917 --> 13:06.885
Listen, we'll get you a spot on
defense, foreign relations.

13:06.887 --> 13:08.419
We'll take care of you.
I promise.

13:08.421 --> 13:09.654
But you have to
step aside.

13:12.759 --> 13:14.526
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

13:16.062 --> 13:17.595
[ knock on window ]

13:17.597 --> 13:18.830
Wake her up!

13:18.832 --> 13:20.732
-What?
-Olivia! Go upstairs,

13:20.734 --> 13:22.734
Separate her from that
presidential spoon,

13:22.736 --> 13:24.435
And you drag her ass
out of bed.
What's happening?

13:24.437 --> 13:26.137
Armageddon, abby.
Armageddon is happening.

13:26.139 --> 13:27.138
<i> ...The presidential affair</i>
<i> scandal</i>

13:27.140 --> 13:28.273
<i> That has gripped the nation.</i>

13:28.275 --> 13:30.275
As it turns out,
the president liked it,

13:30.277 --> 13:32.343
And he did, indeed,
put a ring on it.

13:32.345 --> 13:33.912
Sources have revealed
the president gave ms. Pope

13:33.914 --> 13:35.613
A family heirloom,

13:35.615 --> 13:38.116
A diamond ring apparently passed
down from his grandmother.

13:38.118 --> 13:40.185
Well, the true significance
of the gift is, of course,

13:40.187 --> 13:42.120
Known only to the president
and ms. Pope,

13:42.122 --> 13:44.088
But a ring
is certainly symbolic.

13:44.090 --> 13:46.291
What is the first rule?

13:46.293 --> 13:47.892
Your first rule?

13:49.763 --> 13:50.762
Do not lie.

13:50.764 --> 13:53.531
Do not lie!

13:53.533 --> 13:55.533
Olivia pope, woman of
the people -- she is gone!

13:55.535 --> 13:58.269
She is history!

13:58.271 --> 14:01.606
It's time for olivia pope,
lovestruck teenager.

14:01.608 --> 14:03.675
-I can't sell that.
-You<i> will</i> sell that.

14:03.677 --> 14:06.277
You will sit down with
an interviewer of my choice,

14:06.279 --> 14:08.313
And you will speak as if you
were chatting with your bestie

14:08.315 --> 14:12.116
About your innocent
and uncontrollably doe-eyed love

14:12.118 --> 14:13.818
For the president
of the united states.

14:13.820 --> 14:15.553
That is the plan.

14:15.555 --> 14:17.522
That is the only way
to spin your way

14:17.524 --> 14:21.893
Out of the diamond ring
you neglected to tell me about!

14:26.533 --> 14:27.632
<i> Does this mean</i>
<i> that the president</i>

14:27.634 --> 14:28.666
<i> Is both engaged and married?</i>

14:28.668 --> 14:30.235
<i> No one is certain,</i>

14:30.237 --> 14:31.903
<i> But there are a lot of</i>
<i> questions here tonight, mike.</i>

14:31.905 --> 14:33.071
<i> Back to you in the studio.</i>

14:36.042 --> 14:38.509
This is amazing.

14:38.511 --> 14:41.246
Astounding. Amazing.

14:41.248 --> 14:43.882
I don't know how the hell
they found out about that ring.

14:43.884 --> 14:47.252
But [sighs]
she's actually managed

14:47.254 --> 14:49.754
To go from being a slut
to an everywoman

14:49.756 --> 14:52.056
To your sister-wife
in under 48 hours.

14:52.058 --> 14:54.492
I didn't even know
that was possible.

15:01.234 --> 15:03.835
They threw you off
the judiciary committee.

15:03.837 --> 15:06.571
Me.

15:09.276 --> 15:12.110
That's how they found out
about the ring.

15:12.112 --> 15:14.279
From me.

15:16.283 --> 15:18.850
That's a real
big-girl move.

15:25.859 --> 15:28.293
I got sparkling wine.

15:28.295 --> 15:30.194
I got five different kinds
of cheeses.

15:30.196 --> 15:33.264
Prosciutto, pâté.

15:33.266 --> 15:36.301
I'm gorging on brownies.

15:36.303 --> 15:38.403
[ chuckles ]

15:38.405 --> 15:41.773
♪♪

15:43.777 --> 15:44.876
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

15:46.579 --> 15:48.012
Gibson: Mr. Walker.

15:49.983 --> 15:52.050
Mind if we steal
a minute?

15:53.753 --> 15:55.086
Marcus:
This is a joke, right?

15:55.088 --> 15:57.155
I've been working there
for two days.

15:57.157 --> 15:59.090
If olivia or her people
did anything illegal,

15:59.092 --> 16:00.658
I don't know anything about it,
so go ahead.

16:00.660 --> 16:03.394
Subpoena me.
I can't be bullied.

16:03.396 --> 16:06.564
All due respect, you've
never met bullies like us.

16:06.566 --> 16:08.399
You will help us
get to the truth

16:08.401 --> 16:10.468
Or we will sift through
every inch of your past

16:10.470 --> 16:13.905
Until we find something,
anything, to hang you with.

16:13.907 --> 16:15.440
And if for some reason
you come up clean,

16:15.442 --> 16:18.309
We'll do the same to your
brother, your cousins, friends,

16:18.311 --> 16:21.179
Anyone you ever
cared about.

16:21.181 --> 16:23.648
You think your career
is in a shambles now?

16:23.650 --> 16:26.451
You want me to be a spy.

16:26.453 --> 16:28.186
I want you to be
a good citizen.

16:28.188 --> 16:30.488
If olivia pope and her people
are obstructing justice,

16:30.490 --> 16:31.622
We want to know about it.

16:31.624 --> 16:33.992
So, no, mr. Walker.

16:33.994 --> 16:37.362
This is absolutely not
a joke.

16:37.364 --> 16:39.364
♪♪

16:39.366 --> 16:40.865
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

16:40.867 --> 16:42.967
[ knock on door ]

16:42.969 --> 16:44.369
Hi.

16:44.371 --> 16:46.037
What's up?

16:46.039 --> 16:47.372
You gonna let me in?

16:47.374 --> 16:49.607
-It's not the best time.
-You need to let me in

16:49.609 --> 16:53.011
Because my posse is up to
27 reporters, a dozen bloggers,

16:53.013 --> 16:54.879
40 relentless bearded men
with cameras,

16:54.881 --> 16:57.882
And two dogs that are apparently
world-famous on instagram.

16:57.884 --> 17:00.551
They're probably two
minutes from coming
up those stairs, so...

17:05.458 --> 17:07.125
Come on in.

17:09.462 --> 17:10.528
Olivia pope.

17:10.530 --> 17:12.330
-I know.
-Oh.

17:12.332 --> 17:14.665
Jake has said so many
wonderful things about you.

17:14.667 --> 17:16.801
But television
does you no favors.

17:18.371 --> 17:20.872
Elise is an old friend
from paris.

17:20.874 --> 17:23.041
I bet you two have a lot
to catch up on.

17:25.211 --> 17:26.711
Bye.

17:36.189 --> 17:38.389
Old friend?

17:38.391 --> 17:40.658
Old friend.

17:40.660 --> 17:42.593
You're the most hunted woman
in the world,

17:42.595 --> 17:45.563
And you just decided
to drop by?

17:47.500 --> 17:51.836
I have to go on tv and sell
a love story, make a valentine.

17:51.838 --> 17:54.939
Pretend I got struck
by cupid's arrow

17:54.941 --> 17:56.240
And i've been
staring at fitz

17:56.242 --> 17:58.976
With hearts in my eyes
ever since.

18:00.280 --> 18:01.446
Okay.

18:01.448 --> 18:02.847
Okay?

18:02.849 --> 18:03.948
Well, you're saying it
like it's a problem.

18:03.950 --> 18:06.384
It is.
It's not me.

18:06.386 --> 18:07.585
[ chuckles ]

18:07.587 --> 18:10.388
You love him, right?

18:10.390 --> 18:11.923
Yes.

18:11.925 --> 18:13.357
You threw yourself
in front of a pack of reporters

18:13.359 --> 18:14.759
And publicly said
that you were

18:14.761 --> 18:16.594
In a relationship
with the president, right?

18:16.596 --> 18:18.062
I did.

18:18.064 --> 18:20.231
It's probably your only way
out of this mess.

18:20.233 --> 18:21.966
-Right?
-Maybe.

18:21.968 --> 18:26.104
Yeah.
Then I don't see the problem.

18:31.911 --> 18:34.545
Unless
<i> you're</i> the problem.

18:34.547 --> 18:36.447
What?

18:36.449 --> 18:39.984
If you do this, if you sell
this love story on national tv,

18:39.986 --> 18:42.954
All of your exits
become walled off.

18:42.956 --> 18:45.656
You will be tied to
the white house -- and him --

18:45.658 --> 18:47.125
For the rest of your life,

18:47.127 --> 18:48.659
And that is absolutely
terrifying to you.

18:48.661 --> 18:51.329
I don't blame you.

18:51.331 --> 18:53.297
I'm gonna go.

18:53.299 --> 18:56.400
If it's not that,
what is it?

19:04.844 --> 19:07.912
What if it<i> is</i> that?

19:10.650 --> 19:12.316
Then I see your problem.

19:14.354 --> 19:15.820
Just tell the truth,
olivia.

19:15.822 --> 19:18.022
[ sighs ]

19:18.024 --> 19:20.691
Tell your story.
Tell the world...

19:20.693 --> 19:22.660
How you really feel
about him.

19:22.662 --> 19:26.063
♪♪

19:32.972 --> 19:34.839
[ indistinct whispering ]

19:45.051 --> 19:47.084
There a password
for this secret meeting?

19:49.822 --> 19:52.023
Quinn: Close the door.

19:52.025 --> 19:54.692
Look, leo's p.R. Plan
is too unreliable.

19:54.694 --> 19:56.527
-We need a backstop.
-Assurances.

19:56.529 --> 19:58.062
Guaranteed support
from the committee.

19:58.064 --> 19:59.063
Backroom dealing?

19:59.065 --> 20:00.798
More like
planting evidence.

20:00.800 --> 20:02.833
Honey traps, extortion,
coercive actions --

20:02.835 --> 20:04.902
Whatever we can use
to turn them to our side.

20:04.904 --> 20:05.937
You okay with that,
marcus?

20:08.341 --> 20:11.209
I thought a lot about what
you guys said, and you're right.

20:11.211 --> 20:13.044
I want to be
a good citizen.

20:13.046 --> 20:15.313
That's great to hear,
mr. Walker.

20:15.315 --> 20:17.515
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

20:17.517 --> 20:20.651
And you need to smile
when you say his name -- fitz.

20:20.653 --> 20:23.321
I'm not asking you to
jump up and down on a couch.

20:23.323 --> 20:25.690
Just a little more smiling --
fitz.

20:25.692 --> 20:27.191
See?

20:27.193 --> 20:28.259
Please stop that.

20:29.529 --> 20:31.162
Much has been made
of that ring,

20:31.164 --> 20:33.397
The one on your left forefinger
there.

20:33.399 --> 20:34.832
Yes.
[ clears throat ]

20:34.834 --> 20:36.601
It was a gift
from the president.

20:36.603 --> 20:37.602
An engagement ring?

20:37.604 --> 20:38.736
No.

20:38.738 --> 20:40.538
Just a gift.

20:40.540 --> 20:43.574
It belonged to his
great-grandmother, annette.

20:43.576 --> 20:45.610
She was french.

20:45.612 --> 20:48.379
Her father bought it for her
at an auction in paris.

20:48.381 --> 20:51.182
She wore it
to her debutante ball.

20:51.184 --> 20:54.719
She gave it to president grant
before she died, so...

20:54.721 --> 20:56.921
And then
he gave it to you.

20:56.923 --> 20:59.857
Yes.
He wanted me to have it.

20:59.859 --> 21:03.060
I was touched
when he gave it to me.

21:03.062 --> 21:06.297
I teared up when he told me
the story behind it.

21:06.299 --> 21:08.232
It was...

21:08.234 --> 21:12.203
One of those fairy-tale moments
you see in the movies.

21:12.205 --> 21:13.304
[ chuckles ]

21:13.306 --> 21:16.440
And mrs. Grant
never noticed it?

21:16.442 --> 21:18.876
There are photos of you
wearing it in her presence.

21:21.114 --> 21:23.281
I regret that.

21:23.283 --> 21:24.715
And what about getting involved
with the president

21:24.717 --> 21:26.450
In the first place?

21:26.452 --> 21:28.152
Do you regret that?

21:40.767 --> 21:43.301
I wish
i never laid eyes on him.

21:43.303 --> 21:44.435
On president grant?

21:44.437 --> 21:45.903
I wish we never met.

21:45.905 --> 21:48.072
If we never...

21:48.074 --> 21:50.741
[ sighs ]

21:55.081 --> 21:58.616
I can't tell you
how hard it's been

21:58.618 --> 22:03.521
To watch my friends,
my family, my acquaintances

22:03.523 --> 22:05.790
Being dragged into the spotlight
because of me,

22:05.792 --> 22:09.794
Clients being investigated
and harassed by the media

22:09.796 --> 22:12.330
Because of me,

22:12.332 --> 22:15.333
Loved ones potentially having to
drain their savings

22:15.335 --> 22:18.436
To hire lawyers and
face congressional committees

22:18.438 --> 22:19.937
Because of me.

22:19.939 --> 22:22.840
I wish i'd never
laid eyes on him because of them

22:22.842 --> 22:25.843
And what they are going through
right now.

22:28.214 --> 22:31.182
But also because...

22:33.219 --> 22:36.887
...I've worked very hard
to build a business,

22:36.889 --> 22:39.857
A business
whose only aim

22:39.859 --> 22:44.862
Is to help people become
the best version of themselves,

22:44.864 --> 22:47.631
To stand in their truths

22:47.633 --> 22:50.034
And face the consequences
of their actions

22:50.036 --> 22:53.237
So they can gain forgiveness
and move past their mistakes.

22:53.239 --> 22:54.739
Building that business
was hard work.

22:54.741 --> 22:57.641
I didn't do it alone,
but I built that business.

22:57.643 --> 23:01.178
And it's something i'm proud of,
something that...

23:01.180 --> 23:03.247
Could all go away

23:03.249 --> 23:05.983
Because I laid eyes
on that man,

23:05.985 --> 23:09.754
That married man.

23:09.756 --> 23:12.156
If I never laid eyes
on him,

23:12.158 --> 23:14.358
Then I wouldn't have
fallen in love

23:14.360 --> 23:16.093
And he wouldn't have
fallen in love.

23:16.095 --> 23:18.929
That may have made for two more
lonely people in this world,

23:18.931 --> 23:21.332
But also a lot...

23:21.334 --> 23:23.934
Less pain...

23:23.936 --> 23:28.973
And heartache
for many, many others.

23:31.444 --> 23:37.548
Senator grant
and the grant children,

23:37.550 --> 23:38.682
For the people I love,

23:38.684 --> 23:41.385
For this country
that I love,

23:41.387 --> 23:44.955
A country that expects us
in washington to solve problems,

23:44.957 --> 23:46.056
Not make them,

23:46.058 --> 23:49.960
Is -- is the love
of two people worth...

23:49.962 --> 23:53.898
All this destruction,
all this attention?

23:53.900 --> 23:55.699
I mean,
if it were a choice,

23:55.701 --> 23:58.903
Who would choose
this kind of love?

23:58.905 --> 24:01.739
So I wish we never met.

24:01.741 --> 24:02.773
But we did.

24:06.212 --> 24:08.412
And I tried.

24:08.414 --> 24:14.985
I tried and failed
and tried and...

24:14.987 --> 24:20.424
Failed again to hide,
to stop loving him,

24:20.426 --> 24:22.259
But I couldn't.

24:22.261 --> 24:24.328
I was weak.

24:24.330 --> 24:25.830
I hated myself.

24:25.832 --> 24:30.634
I-i wore this ring
to remind me of my weakness.

24:30.636 --> 24:34.238
And when our affair
was exposed,

24:34.240 --> 24:37.007
I had to follow my own advice
and stand in my truth,

24:37.009 --> 24:40.511
To own who I am,
to accept my faults.

24:40.513 --> 24:42.112
And I won't
ask for forgiveness.

24:42.114 --> 24:44.815
Just don't ask me to...

24:44.817 --> 24:46.250
Undo the past.

24:46.252 --> 24:48.786
Don't ask me to fall out of love
with fitzgerald grant,

24:48.788 --> 24:51.222
Because if I could,
I would.

24:57.263 --> 24:59.964
Does that
answer your question?

24:59.966 --> 25:03.033
♪♪

25:11.777 --> 25:12.843
Woman:
<i> This was a home run.</i>

25:12.845 --> 25:14.044
<i> The kind of tv moment</i>
<i> that could</i>

25:14.046 --> 25:15.546
<i> Go down in american</i>
<i> political history.</i>

25:15.548 --> 25:17.948
<i> Pope did</i>
<i> what she had to do,</i>

25:17.950 --> 25:20.217
<i> Which was to make</i>
<i> herself relatable to</i>
<i> the american public.</i>

25:20.219 --> 25:22.286
<i> But historic?</i>
<i> Look, i-i don't think so.</i>

25:22.288 --> 25:24.021
<i> No, come on.</i>
<i> Ernie, this is no longer</i>

25:24.023 --> 25:27.024
<i> About some ambitious,</i>
<i> home-wrecking bimbo.</i>

25:27.026 --> 25:28.626
<i> This is a story</i>
<i> about co-workers</i>

25:28.628 --> 25:30.461
<i> Who couldn't help but</i>
<i> fall in love with each other.</i>

25:30.463 --> 25:31.795
<i> Be that as it may...</i>

25:31.797 --> 25:36.634
Well, there's actually one thing
olivia and I agree on.

25:36.636 --> 25:38.636
I wish they'd never met,
too.

25:38.638 --> 25:40.638
[ scoffs ]

25:43.910 --> 25:46.310
I'm sorry.

25:46.312 --> 25:48.579
What for?

25:48.581 --> 25:51.715
I brought her on
to the campaign.

25:51.717 --> 25:53.417
[ sighs ]

25:53.419 --> 25:56.053
I think about that
from time to time.

25:56.055 --> 25:58.756
I'm the reason
why all this happened.

26:01.994 --> 26:05.362
They might never have met
if not for me.

26:05.364 --> 26:09.366
And for that...

26:09.368 --> 26:11.936
I am deeply sorry.

26:19.245 --> 26:21.245
Thank you, cyrus.

26:30.923 --> 26:32.957
We have a problem.

26:32.959 --> 26:36.927
What's going on?

26:36.929 --> 26:38.062
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

26:38.064 --> 26:40.130
It's a photo of the committee's
evidence log.

26:40.132 --> 26:41.599
I can see that.
Where'd you get this?

26:41.601 --> 26:43.901
-Moskowitz's office.
-Her office?

26:43.903 --> 26:46.136
She approached me, asked me to
be her eyes and ears in here,

26:46.138 --> 26:47.471
Threw a couple threats
at me.

26:47.473 --> 26:48.973
I let her think
I was cooperating,

26:48.975 --> 26:50.608
Used that as a cover
to collect a little intel.

26:50.610 --> 26:52.476
It's all cia documents,
notes from a meeting

26:52.478 --> 26:54.478
With the president and
the cia director on the night --

26:54.480 --> 26:56.480
-Forward that picture to me.
-Where are you going?

26:56.482 --> 26:57.715
Liv!

26:59.619 --> 27:00.985
[ door slams ]

27:00.987 --> 27:02.886
They committee has the tape,
doesn't it?

27:02.888 --> 27:04.054
My kidnapping.

27:04.056 --> 27:05.789
I'm gonna pretend
you didn't ask me that

27:05.791 --> 27:07.891
And allow you to turn around
and walk out that door.

27:07.893 --> 27:09.159
David,
if they have that tape,

27:09.161 --> 27:12.563
Then we are all going down,
you included.

27:12.565 --> 27:15.065
You signed that warrant
for the raid of the warehouse.

27:15.067 --> 27:17.434
You provided favors
to my mother, a terrorist,

27:17.436 --> 27:18.636
To gain access
to the auction.

27:18.638 --> 27:20.270
You're in this, david.

27:20.272 --> 27:21.805
And if i'm being honest,

27:21.807 --> 27:25.275
You're probably the only one
who doesn't deserve to be.

27:25.277 --> 27:29.246
Your voice is calm, measured.
You're complimenting me.

27:29.248 --> 27:31.682
Is this some new genius way
of putting the screws to me?

27:31.684 --> 27:32.850
David, I need to know
if they have that tape

27:32.852 --> 27:34.918
So that I can protect us.

27:37.590 --> 27:39.156
Do they have
the tape?!

27:44.597 --> 27:48.298
Some dogged aide picked through
the pile of documents

27:48.300 --> 27:51.502
They got from the white house,
found some e-mail exchange

27:51.504 --> 27:54.538
Between the president
and cia director lowry

27:54.540 --> 27:58.375
About a meeting they'd had
to discuss the "o.P. Matter."

27:58.377 --> 28:00.444
Hoping that didn't stand for
"orange peel,"

28:00.446 --> 28:02.212
Moskowitz and gibson
subpoenaed

28:02.214 --> 28:04.448
All documentation
related to that meeting

28:04.450 --> 28:08.118
And managed to unearth
the mother of all smoking guns.

28:08.120 --> 28:10.387
The good news --
it doesn't mean anything unless

28:10.389 --> 28:13.390
Someone can corroborate that
the president watched the video.

28:15.561 --> 28:17.294
He confided in someone?

28:17.296 --> 28:19.029
Who was it?

28:19.031 --> 28:20.898
Who'd he tell?

28:20.900 --> 28:23.801
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

28:35.147 --> 28:37.147
Hi.

28:37.149 --> 28:39.183
Hi.

28:39.185 --> 28:40.884
We're listening to
records?

28:40.886 --> 28:42.753
We are listening to
records.

28:42.755 --> 28:44.488
Hopefully that's not
all we're doing.

28:44.490 --> 28:46.690
[ marvin gaye's
"let's get it on" plays ]

28:46.692 --> 28:52.529
♪ i've been really tryin',
baby ♪

28:52.531 --> 28:58.202
♪ tryin' to hold back
this feeling for so long ♪

28:58.204 --> 29:03.273
♪ and if you feel
like I feel, baby ♪

29:03.275 --> 29:04.942
♪ then come on ♪

29:04.944 --> 29:07.277
♪ oh, come on ♪

29:07.279 --> 29:08.178
♪ whoo ♪

29:08.180 --> 29:10.881
♪ let's get it on ♪

29:10.883 --> 29:13.283
♪ ah, baby ♪
[ moans ]

29:13.285 --> 29:16.687
♪ let's get it on ♪

29:16.689 --> 29:19.723
♪ let's love, baby ♪

29:19.725 --> 29:25.295
♪ let's get it on, sugar ♪

29:25.297 --> 29:27.765
♪ let's get it on ♪

29:27.767 --> 29:29.566
They know about
west angola.

29:29.568 --> 29:32.903
♪ whoo hoo ♪

29:32.905 --> 29:36.640
♪ we're all sensitive people ♪

29:36.642 --> 29:39.376
♪ with so much to give ♪
the senators?

29:39.378 --> 29:43.547
♪ understand me, sugar ♪
they have the tape of me
from when I was taken.

29:43.549 --> 29:45.082
That's impossible.

29:45.084 --> 29:46.416
They found something
in the documents you gave them.

29:46.418 --> 29:48.051
It led them to the cia.

29:48.053 --> 29:49.787
-How do you know all this?
-It doesn't matter.

29:49.789 --> 29:51.722
I know.

29:51.724 --> 29:55.225
♪ I love you ♪

29:55.227 --> 29:58.896
♪ there's nothing wrong
with me ♪
going to war for your mistress
is an impeachable offense.

29:58.898 --> 30:01.098
That tape is all the proof
they need.

30:01.100 --> 30:05.169
♪ loving you, baby, no, no ♪
so we find a way
around it.

30:05.171 --> 30:07.237
We can say
it's been doctored.

30:07.239 --> 30:09.439
♪ and giving yourself to me ♪
and no one will buy it.

30:09.441 --> 30:10.607
♪ can never be wrong ♪
then I never saw it.

30:10.609 --> 30:11.642
What?

30:11.644 --> 30:13.777
♪ if the love is true ♪

30:13.779 --> 30:16.747
♪ oh, baby ♪
I never saw the tape.
I never knew you were taken.

30:16.749 --> 30:18.816
♪ whoo hoo ♪
the war...

30:18.818 --> 30:20.017
Had nothing
to do with you.

30:20.019 --> 30:22.252
♪ don't you know how sweet ♪
that could work.

30:22.254 --> 30:23.987
♪ and wonderful ♪
it<i> will</i> work.

30:23.989 --> 30:26.356
♪ life can be ♪
as long as cyrus
doesn't say otherwise.

30:26.358 --> 30:28.458
Cyrus is the only person
that connects you to that tape.

30:28.460 --> 30:29.493
He can say you saw it.

30:29.495 --> 30:30.494
He wouldn't.

30:30.496 --> 30:32.462
♪ i'm asking you, baby ♪

30:32.464 --> 30:33.864
[ sighs ]
okay, he would.

30:33.866 --> 30:35.299
♪ to get it on with me ♪

30:35.301 --> 30:37.601
[ record scratches ]
♪ to get it on with me ♪

30:37.603 --> 30:39.303
♪ to get it on with me ♪

30:39.305 --> 30:40.838
♪ to get it on with me ♪

30:40.840 --> 30:42.639
♪ to get it on with me ♪

30:42.641 --> 30:43.674
♪ to get it on with me ♪

30:43.676 --> 30:44.741
♪ to get it on with me ♪

30:49.348 --> 30:50.380
[ laughs ]
we should have locked ourselves
in a room

30:50.382 --> 30:52.049
And gotten drunk together
years ago.

30:52.051 --> 30:53.383
I haven't had
this much fun

30:53.385 --> 30:56.620
Spending the night with a woman,
hell, ever.

30:56.622 --> 30:59.189
[ both laugh ]

30:59.191 --> 31:00.858
Oh.

31:04.530 --> 31:05.896
You should
come and work for me.

31:05.898 --> 31:07.364
A junior senator?

31:07.366 --> 31:09.132
Not for long, not if you
come and work for me.

31:09.134 --> 31:10.033
[ cellphone rings ]

31:10.035 --> 31:12.169
[ laughs ]

31:12.171 --> 31:14.171
Hello?

31:14.173 --> 31:15.205
Charlotte: Mr. Beene?

31:15.207 --> 31:16.773
Please hold for the president.

31:17.576 --> 31:19.243
Who is it?

31:19.245 --> 31:20.377
Nobody.

31:20.379 --> 31:21.879
It's just a friend.

31:26.585 --> 31:29.586
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

31:29.588 --> 31:31.555
I saw your interview.
It was good.

31:31.557 --> 31:33.757
You were good.
You were you.

31:37.263 --> 31:39.329
So, where's your old friend
tonight?

31:39.331 --> 31:41.098
She had a meeting.

31:41.100 --> 31:43.333
How do you know her?

31:43.335 --> 31:44.801
She's my wife.

31:50.075 --> 31:51.541
You never told me that.

31:51.543 --> 31:53.410
You never asked.

31:53.412 --> 31:56.780
Hmm.

31:56.782 --> 31:58.415
I'm asking now.

31:58.417 --> 32:00.751
About my wife?

32:00.753 --> 32:04.221
Yes,
as ridiculous as that sounds.

32:04.223 --> 32:05.923
Uh, she's great.

32:07.893 --> 32:09.760
[ laughs ]

32:09.762 --> 32:10.894
That's good.

32:10.896 --> 32:11.862
Yeah. You'd like her.

32:11.864 --> 32:13.697
Okay.

32:13.699 --> 32:14.865
Is this the part
where you say --

32:14.867 --> 32:15.966
She's a lot like you?

32:18.637 --> 32:20.237
Not sure
how to respond to that.

32:20.239 --> 32:21.872
Guess that means
you have a type.

32:21.874 --> 32:23.373
So do you.

32:23.375 --> 32:25.175
Married guys.

32:27.313 --> 32:29.379
[ laughs ]

32:29.381 --> 32:31.114
Did you get extra --

32:33.385 --> 32:35.652
Thanks.

32:38.424 --> 32:40.290
Cy.

32:40.292 --> 32:41.591
Mr. President.

32:41.593 --> 32:42.826
Have a seat.

32:45.597 --> 32:46.730
Why am I here?

32:48.600 --> 32:50.267
I want you back.

32:50.269 --> 32:51.501
Back?

32:51.503 --> 32:53.403
In the white house.

32:53.405 --> 32:55.605
Here. Working for me.

32:55.607 --> 32:58.075
You're offering me
my job back?

32:58.077 --> 33:00.310
I have a chief of staff,
but yes, something similar.

33:00.312 --> 33:02.312
High level.
Senior adviser.

33:02.314 --> 33:04.848
Why?

33:04.850 --> 33:07.084
Because I could use you
right now.

33:07.086 --> 33:09.353
The country could use you.

33:09.355 --> 33:11.822
We have unfinished business
in this administration,

33:11.824 --> 33:14.091
And I want you
to be a part of it.

33:14.093 --> 33:17.194
I know we've had
some difficulties recently.

33:17.196 --> 33:19.930
I think we both acted
emotionally and precipitously.

33:19.932 --> 33:22.265
I want to put that behind us
for the good of the country.

33:22.267 --> 33:24.167
I want you on my team.

33:24.169 --> 33:25.335
Difficulties?

33:25.337 --> 33:26.670
Yes.
Hmm.

33:29.775 --> 33:31.708
This is interesting.

33:35.280 --> 33:37.781
What do they have?

33:37.783 --> 33:39.983
What?

33:39.985 --> 33:41.451
The senate committee.
They have something on you.

33:41.453 --> 33:42.719
That's why i'm here.

33:42.721 --> 33:43.787
I don't know
what you're talking about.

33:43.789 --> 33:46.523
It's not the ring.
She fixed that.

33:46.525 --> 33:48.792
It's bigger than that.
What is it?

33:48.794 --> 33:51.862
-Cy --
-amanda tanner, maybe?

33:51.864 --> 33:53.697
Remington?
Do they know about rowan?

33:53.699 --> 33:55.532
Defiance?

33:56.802 --> 33:58.301
Oh, no.

33:58.303 --> 34:00.070
It's the tape.

34:00.072 --> 34:02.239
West angola.

34:02.241 --> 34:03.840
Oh, I see.

34:03.842 --> 34:06.343
That's really not good,
is it?

34:06.345 --> 34:08.812
But this?
This is good.

34:08.814 --> 34:10.814
This is her, not you.
It's smart.

34:10.816 --> 34:12.682
I'm the only one
who can say you saw it.

34:12.684 --> 34:14.084
Well, me
and the vegetable andrew,

34:14.086 --> 34:17.320
But he's just drooling now,
so it's just me.

34:17.322 --> 34:21.725
You give me back my job --
or some job --

34:21.727 --> 34:23.660
And I say
i never saw the tape.

34:23.662 --> 34:24.995
That's the deal, right?

34:24.997 --> 34:26.763
Yes.

34:26.765 --> 34:28.665
What do you say?

34:35.274 --> 34:38.241
How many times did you
mispronounce "delano"

34:38.243 --> 34:39.676
In that governor's debate?

34:39.678 --> 34:41.445
-Excuse me?
-Against astley.

34:41.447 --> 34:43.613
You kept saying
the city of "dell-ano"

34:43.615 --> 34:44.681
Instead of
the city of "de-layno."

34:44.683 --> 34:46.216
Do you remember?

34:46.218 --> 34:48.618
No, I have no idea. That was
16 years ago in the primary --

34:48.620 --> 34:50.554
It was 17 years ago,
and it wasn't the primary.

34:50.556 --> 34:52.789
It was the general,
the second debate.

34:52.791 --> 34:53.757
You fumbled it
three times --

34:53.759 --> 34:55.625
Twice
in the first five minutes

34:55.627 --> 34:57.594
And once again
about 45 minutes later.

34:57.596 --> 34:59.062
But you caught yourself
that last time,

34:59.064 --> 35:00.430
And you
never did it again.

35:00.432 --> 35:02.766
And you carried kern county
by 11 points.

35:02.768 --> 35:04.868
Did you know you carried
kern county by 11 points?

35:04.870 --> 35:06.636
Why are we talking about this,
cyrus?

35:06.638 --> 35:08.638
Because I want to. If you
don't want to talk about it,

35:08.640 --> 35:11.775
I can leave and you can rehearse
your resignation speech.

35:15.247 --> 35:16.480
Do you remember
what you ate

35:16.482 --> 35:18.448
The morning after you become
governor of california?

35:18.450 --> 35:19.583
No.

35:19.585 --> 35:20.917
I remember.

35:20.919 --> 35:22.919
You had a doughnut,
a cinnamon doughnut,

35:22.921 --> 35:24.788
Which was weird because
you didn't eat doughnuts.

35:24.790 --> 35:27.290
You wanted yogurt and fruit
that morning -- a parfait --

35:27.292 --> 35:29.659
And you wanted to eat it at some
snooty place in santa barbara,

35:29.661 --> 35:30.994
But I said no.

35:30.996 --> 35:32.162
Why did I say no?

35:32.164 --> 35:33.463
Because I was already
looking ahead

35:33.465 --> 35:36.233
Because governor of california
wasn't the goal.

35:36.235 --> 35:39.102
So we drove over the hill
into ranch country,

35:39.104 --> 35:42.506
Into real-people country, to
the longhorn café in santa ynez,

35:42.508 --> 35:45.976
Where you would be seen eating
a doughnut like a real person.

35:45.978 --> 35:48.345
I picked out
your doughnut.

35:48.347 --> 35:50.013
It was cinnamon.

35:50.015 --> 35:51.915
But then I snuck into
the kitchen and got
you a bowl of fruit

35:51.917 --> 35:52.949
Because I didn't want you
to whine --

35:52.951 --> 35:54.818
Some oranges and apples
and berries.

35:54.820 --> 35:56.786
I removed the bananas,
of course,

35:56.788 --> 35:59.022
Because
you don't like bananas.

35:59.024 --> 36:02.025
And you ate the fruit
in the car on the ride home.

36:02.027 --> 36:04.828
Do you remember
the ride home?

36:04.830 --> 36:06.163
No.

36:06.165 --> 36:08.665
I remember you had fruit,
but you didn't finish it

36:08.667 --> 36:11.768
Because you said
it smelled like banana.

36:11.770 --> 36:17.340
This is
what I know...About you.

36:17.342 --> 36:20.310
This is what I remember.
This is what is in my head.

36:20.312 --> 36:23.046
You.

36:23.048 --> 36:25.315
Everywhere, everything,
what you say,

36:25.317 --> 36:29.019
What you eat, what you wear,
what you think.

36:29.021 --> 36:32.222
I dream your dreams
and I sweat your nightmares.

36:32.224 --> 36:35.058
This is
what you are to me.

36:35.060 --> 36:36.359
And what am I to you?

36:36.361 --> 36:39.029
I am the man to be
thrown on the grenade

36:39.031 --> 36:41.198
And the guy you use
and abuse and toss out

36:41.200 --> 36:43.667
And try desperately to reel back
in to save you one more time.

36:43.669 --> 36:47.370
That is what I am to you.
That is all you know about me.

36:47.372 --> 36:49.206
If I left this room,

36:49.208 --> 36:51.641
You wouldn't even remember
I was here,

36:51.643 --> 36:54.544
But I could tell you
everything you said,

36:54.546 --> 36:56.913
The color of your shirt,
the part of your hair.

36:56.915 --> 36:58.315
I can look in your eyes

36:58.317 --> 37:01.651
And know how you slept
the night before.

37:01.653 --> 37:04.354
I know
exactly how many times

37:04.356 --> 37:07.090
You mispronounced a single word
in a debate 17 years ago,

37:07.092 --> 37:08.858
And you couldn't tell me
my mother's name.

37:08.860 --> 37:12.929
I know
why we're sitting here --

37:12.931 --> 37:15.932
To fill in
this olivia pope masterpiece.

37:15.934 --> 37:17.767
I get a job, some job.

37:17.769 --> 37:19.669
You get to keep yours.

37:19.671 --> 37:23.873
We all march forward
into glory.

37:23.875 --> 37:26.109
All is forgotten.

37:26.111 --> 37:29.846
That's the deal on the table,
and i'm not going to take it.

37:33.385 --> 37:36.453
Because this band is never,
ever getting back together.

37:40.025 --> 37:44.094
I do not need this.

37:44.096 --> 37:46.263
[ scoffs ]

37:46.265 --> 37:49.065
I do not need you.

37:49.067 --> 37:51.334
Not anymore.

37:55.040 --> 37:58.074
We were on a bus

37:58.076 --> 38:00.710
Between king city and salinas
in my first run for governor,

38:00.712 --> 38:02.812
And you had
a package from her.

38:02.814 --> 38:05.882
It was
an agatha christie novel,

38:05.884 --> 38:08.084
And she'd written
a little review on an index card

38:08.086 --> 38:11.288
And tucked it
inside the front cover.

38:11.290 --> 38:13.790
"i think you're gonna
really like this one, cy,

38:13.792 --> 38:16.893
But I don't know how she
killed him with a candelabra."

38:16.895 --> 38:19.963
You laughed.

38:19.965 --> 38:22.265
You said she sent you
a package like that

38:22.267 --> 38:24.834
Every week
since you left home.

38:24.836 --> 38:26.903
Always a mystery,
usually agatha christie,

38:26.905 --> 38:29.673
And always with a little index
card that ruined the story.

38:29.675 --> 38:32.842
And you loved it.

38:32.844 --> 38:36.179
I used to see you
open those packages,

38:36.181 --> 38:40.016
Behind a campaign bus
in barstow, in your office,

38:40.018 --> 38:42.952
Backstage at a rally
at san marcos high school.

38:42.954 --> 38:48.858
Sometimes it was the only time
i'd see you smile in a week.

38:48.860 --> 38:51.461
Sometimes
in a morning briefing,

38:51.463 --> 38:55.098
I'd know you'd gotten one of
the packages just by your mood.

38:55.100 --> 38:59.836
I know
what she meant to you.

38:59.838 --> 39:02.806
I know
that you loved her.

39:02.808 --> 39:05.508
Your mom's name...

39:05.510 --> 39:06.743
Was helen.

39:10.716 --> 39:13.316
I am sorry.

39:13.318 --> 39:19.055
Truly, deeply sorry.

39:19.057 --> 39:22.158
I am sorry.

39:22.160 --> 39:24.994
I'm sorry
for what happened to us.

39:24.996 --> 39:27.197
I'm sorry
for what<i> i</i> did to us.

39:27.199 --> 39:29.299
We both made some mistakes
along the way,

39:29.301 --> 39:31.501
But your mistakes...

39:31.503 --> 39:34.738
Were for me.

39:34.740 --> 39:39.642
My biggest mistake...

39:39.644 --> 39:42.846
Was forgetting
that we were family.

39:42.848 --> 39:45.982
Everything you did,
you did for me.

39:45.984 --> 39:47.717
♪ birds flying high,
you know how I feel ♪

39:47.719 --> 39:49.586
You are my guy.

39:49.588 --> 39:52.489
♪ sun in the sky ♪

39:52.491 --> 39:56.860
♪ you know how I feel ♪
I can't do this,
not like this, not alone.

39:56.862 --> 39:59.362
♪ reeds driftin' on by ♪

39:59.364 --> 40:02.332
♪ you know how I feel ♪
I want you back.

40:02.334 --> 40:05.602
That seat on the couch
is yours if you want it.

40:05.604 --> 40:08.538
The job
is yours if you want it.

40:08.540 --> 40:10.206
♪ it's a new life for me ♪

40:10.208 --> 40:11.674
Please.

